Sanitize Bedrock tool names to satisfy [a-zA-Z0-9_-]+.

Goose surfaces an MCP tool's display name ("<Extension>: <Title Case>", e.g.
"Scooter-env: Slack Respond") into a message's tool_call.name; on session RESUME
that display-formatted name is reloaded and serialized into the Bedrock `converse`
request's toolUse.name, which Bedrock rejects:

  ValidationException: Value at 'messages.N.member.content.M.member.toolUse.name'
  failed to satisfy constraint: Member must satisfy regular expression pattern:
  [a-zA-Z0-9_-]+

That permanently wedges a conversation that (a) used MCP tools and (b) was resumed —
every subsequent turn replays the invalid name.

Fix: sanitize the tool name to [a-zA-Z0-9_-]+ at the THREE outbound sites that must
agree (the tool *definition* in toolConfig + both toolUse blocks), and keep a lossless
sanitized->original map so the name Bedrock echoes back in its RESPONSE is restored to
the real name before goose dispatches it to MCP (else the tool wouldn't be found).
toolResult blocks pair by tool_use_id (not name), so they need no change.

Upstream note: the analogous OpenAI Responses formatter already sanitizes function-call
names (block/goose#10344); the Bedrock formatter was missed. Carry this as a downstream
overrideAttrs/cargoPatches patch until an upstream-fixed goose is pinned.

